 <subsection xml:id="subsec-Divisibility-test-for-9">
    <title>Divisibility test for 9</title>
    <p>
        A number is divisible by <m>9</m> if the sum of the digits in the number is divisible by <m>9.</m>
    </p>
    <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Activity for divisibility test for 9 goes here.
            </p>
        </statement>
    </activity>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Which of the following numbers are divisible by 9?
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>14\,578</m>, <m>68\,373</m>, <m>103\,689</m>
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                <ol marker="a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>14\,578</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>1+4+5+7+8=25</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>25 \div 9 = 2 \text{ remainder } 7</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>14\,578</m> is not divisible by <m>9</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>68\,373</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>6+8+3+7+3=27</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>27 \div 9 = 3 </m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>68\,373</m> is divisible by <m>9</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                            <p>
                            <m>103\,689</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>1+0+3+6+8+9=27</m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>27 \div 9 = 3 </m>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <m>103\,689</m> is divisible by <m>9</m>
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>68\,373</m> and <m>103\,689</m> are divisible <m>9</m> because the sum of the digits in each number is divisible by <m>9</m>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
